      <MissionDesc>Planned Parenthood Advocates Pasadena and San Gabriel Valley is a 501(c)(4) social welfare organization. Our mission is to preserve and broaden access to reproductive health care through legislation, public education, and electoral activity.</MissionDesc>
      <SignificantNewProgramSrvcInd>0</SignificantNewProgramSrvcInd>
      <SignificantChangeInd>0</SignificantChangeInd>
      <ExpenseAmt>5595</ExpenseAmt>
      <Desc>Legislate: PP Advocates works to introduce and support legislation that protects and expands reproductive health care services, accurate sexual health education, and reproductive rights, and to defeat legislation that restricts access to care or reproductive choice.</Desc>
      <ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp>
        <ExpenseAmt>71651</ExpenseAmt>
        <Desc>Educate: Through community organizing, fundraising and grassroots strength we organize people, mobilize power and stand with communities and groups to take action and ensure an informed electorate. We mobilize a strong network of grassroots supporters and build leadership to sustain the movement for access to reproductive health provided by Planned Parenthood health centers and other providers throughout Pasadena and the San Gabriel Valley. We work to ensure that abortion remains a safe and legal medical procedure and actively work to dismantle abortion stigma.</Desc>
      </ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp>
      <ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp>
        <ExpenseAmt>18580</ExpenseAmt>
        <Desc>Elect: PP Advocates endorses candidates and works to elect lawmakers who will support sexual health education, reproductive health and rights. PP Advocates is a non-partisan organization that endorses and partners with candidates and elected officials who support a full range of reproductive care regardless of political party or affiliation.</Desc>
      </ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp>
